Reasoning: The paper discusses the challenges of analyzing multilingual event-centric data, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR) techniques. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper may also fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) as it deals with analyzing information in the context of cross-cultural studies. Finally, cs.CY (Computers and Society) may also be a relevant sub-category as the paper discusses the impact of ongoing events on local communities.
